Package: pilot-link
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Tools and library for Palm PDA communication
 pilot-link is a suite of tools for communicating with Palm handheld
 devices over serial, USB, and network connections. This package
 contains the command-line utilities and support files.

Package: libpisock9
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: pilot-link (<< 0.13.1-2)
Replaces: pilot-link (<< 0.13.1-2)
Description: library for communicating with Palm devices
 libpisock provides the low-level communication layer used by the
 pilot-link tools and bindings to talk to Palm handheld devices over
 serial, USB, and network connections.

Package: libpisync1
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libpisock9 (= ${binary:Version})
Breaks: pilot-link (<< 0.13.1-2)
Replaces: pilot-link (<< 0.13.1-2)
Description: synchronization library for Palm devices
 libpisync provides synchronization helpers built on top of libpisock
 for use by pilot-link and compatible applications.

Package: libpisock-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, libpisock9 (= ${binary:Version}), libpisync1 (= ${binary:Version})
Breaks: pilot-link (<< 0.13.1-2)
Replaces: pilot-link (<< 0.13.1-2)
Description: development files for libpisock and libpisync
 This package contains the headers, unversioned linker symlinks,
 static libraries, pkg-config metadata, and aclocal macro needed to
 build software against libpisock and libpisync.

Package: python3-pisock
Section: python
Architecture: any
Depends: python3:any, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: python-pisock
Replaces: python-pisock
Description: Python 3 bindings for libpisock
 This package provides Python 3 bindings for libpisock, allowing Python
 applications to communicate with Palm handheld devices using the
 pilot-link libraries.
